dcterms:description: This graph represents the mouse brain. Nodes represent regions of the brain and edges represent neuronal fiber tracts that connect one node to another. It contains no triangles, which is rare in general.

dcterms:description: This graph contains information about flights between airports based on a record of more than 3.5 million US Domestic Flights from 1990 to 2009. Nodes are represented by the 3-letter airport codes.
